cs.CR, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a secure and privacy-preserving object-finding system. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also likely as the system involves multiple mobile users working together to find a lost object. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the system relies on mobile crowdsourcing to locate lost objects. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper mentions extensive simulations to confirm the efficacy and efficiency of the system. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the system relies on Bluetooth tags and mobile devices to communicate and locate lost objects.
